# Second worked example: Cascade — a (fictional) science-explainers publication.
# Proves the toll is publisher-agnostic: a different origin, a different article
# path prefix, and a deeper credits graph, with zero core code changed.
# Copy these over your root .env to point the tollgate at Cascade.

ORIGIN_URL=https://cascade.example
ARTICLE_PATH_PREFIXES=explainers

# Bundled fixture credits graph for a no-backend demo...
CREDITS_FIXTURES=./examples/cascade/credits.json
# ...or resolve live from the publisher's own credits API instead:
# CREDITS_API_URL=https://cascade.example/api
# CREDITS_API_TOKEN=
